Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportIgnoredNets(25.10)                              reportIgnoredNets(25.10)

Name
       reportIgnoredNets - Generates a report that lists the nets that are ig-
       nored  by  timing  optimization (optDesign) or that might impact timing
       closure

Syntax
       reportIgnoredNets

       [-help]

        -outfile <fileName>

       Generates a report that lists the nets that are ignored by timing opti-
       mization (optDesign) or that might impact timing closure. You  can  use
       this command after loading a design with timing constraints.

        The report lists the following types of nets:

              * Nets that are ignored by timing optimization

              * Nets that might impact timing closure but are not ignored

       Nets that are ignored by timing optimization are listed below:

       dontTouchNets
              Nets set as don't touch by the set_dont_touch SDC constraint

       externalNets
              Nets connected to I/O pad or area I/O instances

       topLevelPotentialTriStateNets
              Nets connecting tristate drivers to top-level I/Os

       clockNets
              Nets marked clock by the timing engine

       specialNets
              Nets that have the attribute specialnet

       pwrGndNets
              Nets that have the attribute power/ground

       analogNets
              Nets that have the attribute analog

       noDriverNets
              Nets that do not have a driver

       Fixed Wires/Cover Wires
              Nets that have a Fixed/Cover wire attribute

       Nets  that  might  impact timing closure but are not ignored are listed
       below:

       multiDriverNets
              Nets that have multiple drivers

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each reportIgnoredNets parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man reportIgnoredNets

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies a file name for the report.

Related Information
              * optDesign

              * setOptMode

